Partly cloudy- a bit windy- 3+ inches of rain in the previous 5 days
Overcast- 4" of rain in last week

A little windy but got a good reading.  Partly cloudy- hot and humid. A little windy but got a good reading.  Partly cloudy- hot and humid.  The two Loons on the North end of Lake Millicent finally had two baby's last week.

Weather was calm and beautiful.  We saw the two new baby Loons about 3 weeks old and they were doing well.  Jim Angster from Richmond Virginia was along to observe my wife Amy do the reading.  A beautiful morning- but could be warmer!  It is the end of July!!
A little breezy- cool but nice.  Partly cloudy.  The 2 baby Loons are getting big...about the size of a duck.
Beautiful day early then cooled off fast around 2/3pm

ICE WENT OUT ON THE 8TH FOR THE MOST PART.  VERY NICE MORNING- CALM AND ABOUT 70 DEGREES.  THERE IS A LOT OF DEBRIS IN THE WATER STILL- STICKS- LEAVES- BARK- ETC.  HAPPY MOTHERS DAY TO ALL THE MOTHERS!!
It was partly cloudy and started to rain as we were returning to our dock.  Fairly calm but some wind.
Beautiful- calm morning.  A little overcast.  Loons are nesting down in the bay of Millicent by King's.  Amy does the readings.
Nice day but mostly cloudy.  The loons and the 2 baby's are growing up and out of the bay and into the big lake. All seems well.

Beautiful day- about 80 degrees.  However the pollen from the trees just came last night so it was in the lake and making it green.  My wife- Amy- as always did the reading as I maneuvered the pontoon boat.
EWM has taken over the chain!!!
It was cloudy and raining off and on. My son Ross and his wife Andrea helped Amy and I do the reading.
Partly cloudy and during the eclipse!

Beautyfull day. Calm and sunny. Onterra our consultants were on the lake checking things out. Did find some single plants of EWM in about 16 feet of water in both Busky Bay and Millicent. Hard to believe the clarity of the water- best we have ever seen.
A little windy. Loons with 2 new baby's
Beautiful day- calm blue sky's.  The two baby Loons are quickly growing up on Lake Millicent!
Nice day slight breeze. Partly cloudy
Beautiful day. Loons seen. My wife Amy and Morgan Mellum helped.
